category: DEFINITIONS FROM THE DEVIL'S DICTIONARY
category comment: (Ken: And finally, the satirical work by Ambrose Bierce...)

clue: Under C: "A familiar kitchen-garden vegetable about as large and wise as a man's head"

response: a cabbage

clue: Under H: "An agreeable sensation arising from contemplating the misery of another"

response: happiness

clue: Under P: "A play in which the story is told without violence to the language"

response: a pantomime

clue: Under N: "Appointing your grandmother to office for the good of the party"

response: nepotism

clue: Under Q: "A sufficient number of members of a deliberative body to have their own way and their own way of having it"

response: a quorum

